value all by itself.

00:02:26.400 --> 00:02:29.700 align:middle line:10%
It has value because people
agree that it has value.

00:02:29.700 --> 00:02:32.240 align:middle line:90%


00:02:32.240 --> 00:02:34.940 align:middle line:84%
Economists will tell
you what money does.

00:02:34.940 --> 00:02:37.175 align:middle line:90%
It facilitates exchange.

00:02:37.175 --> 00:02:41.690 align:middle line:84%
You use it to count things
and keep track of things.

00:02:41.690 --> 00:02:45.310 align:middle line:84%
Now, you write some numbers
on a magical piece of paper

00:02:45.310 --> 00:02:46.660 align:middle line:90%
called a check.

00:02:46.660 --> 00:02:50.620 align:middle line:84%
And you can cause all
kinds of abundant goods

00:02:50.620 --> 00:02:53.440 align:middle line:90%
to come to your house.

00:02:53.440 --> 00:02:56.970 align:middle line:84%
And you could even cause
misery for thousands of people

00:02:56.970 --> 00:03:00.060 align:middle line:84%
if you are one of
the highest initiates

00:03:00.060 --> 00:03:04.410 align:middle line:90%
of the magic of money.

00:03:04.410 --> 00:03:06.820 align:middle line:84%
Scarcity is built
into the money system.

00:03:06.820 --> 00:03:10.190 align:middle line:10%
On a most obvious level,
it's because of the way

00:03:10.190 --> 00:03:13.100 align:middle line:10%
money is created as
interest-bearing debt.

00:03:13.100 --> 00:03:16.700 align:middle line:84%
So anytime a bank lends money
into existence or the Federal

00:03:16.700 --> 00:03:20.000 align:middle line:84%
Reserve creates money,
the money comes along

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:22.520 align:middle line:84%
with a corresponding
amount of debt.

00:03:22.520 --> 00:03:24.770 align:middle line:84%
And the debt, because
there's interest on it,

00:03:24.770 --> 00:03:26.940 align:middle line:84%
is always greater than
the amount of money.

00:03:26.940 --> 00:03:28.940 align:middle line:84%
So it essentially throws
people into competition

00:03:28.940 --> 00:03:32.490 align:middle line:84%
with each other for
never enough money.

00:03:32.490 --> 00:03:35.323 align:middle line:84%
Growth is another thing that's
built into our money system.

00:03:35.323 --> 00:03:37.740 align:middle line:10%
If you're a bank, you're going
to lend to the person who's

00:03:37.740 --> 00:03:41.220 align:middle line:10%
going to create new goods and
services so they can profit

00:03:41.220 --> 00:03:42.780 align:middle line:10%
and they can pay you back.

00:03:42.780 --> 00:03:44.780 align:middle line:10%
You're not going to lend
to somebody who doesn't

00:03:44.780 --> 00:03:46.340 align:middle line:10%
create goods and services.

00:03:46.340 --> 00:03:50.988 align:middle line:10%
So money goes toward those who
will create even more of it.

00:03:50.988 --> 00:03:52.530 align:middle line:84%
But, basically,
economic growth means

00:03:52.530 --> 00:03:56.910 align:middle line:84%
that you have to find
something that was once nature

00:03:56.910 --> 00:03:57.930 align:middle line:90%
and make it into a good.

00:03:57.930 --> 00:04:00.800 align:middle line:90%


00:04:00.800 --> 00:04:02.740 align:middle line:84%
Or it was once a
gift relationship

00:04:02.740 --> 00:04:03.940 align:middle line:90%
and make it into a service.

00:04:03.940 --> 00:04:06.760 align:middle line:84%
You have to find something
that people once got for free

00:04:06.760 --> 00:04:09.100 align:middle line:84%
or did for themselves
or for each other

00:04:09.100 --> 00:04:11.790 align:middle line:84%
and then take it away and
sell it back to them somehow.

00:04:11.790 --> 00:04:14.820 align:middle line:90%


00:04:14.820 --> 00:04:17.579 align:middle line:84%
By turning things
into commodities,

00:04:17.579 --> 00:04:20.070 align:middle line:84%
we get cut off from
nature in the same way

00:04:20.070 --> 00:04:21.959 align:middle line:90%
as we're cut off from community.

00:04:21.959 --> 00:04:25.770 align:middle line:84%
We look at nature with eyes
of it's just a bunch of stuff.

00:04:25.770 --> 00:04:29.290 align:middle line:84%
